    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half then peel and slice <strong>most </strong>of your <strong>garlic </strong>(don't chop!) and set aside <strong>half</strong> a <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>clove</strong> per person for later</p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> roughly and drain your <strong>mozzarella </strong>and tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>2/3</strong> of the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and cook for 2 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>spinach & ricotta</strong> <strong>ravioli</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan with the tomatoes</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until very fragrant, breaking up the <strong>'Nduja </strong>with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the 'Nduja cooks, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p><p>Rub the <strong>toasted ciabatta halves </strong>with the <strong>reserved garlic </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>garlicky ciabatta</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining chopped cherry tomatoes </strong>and <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>in a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped basil </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>bruschetta mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining chopped basil</strong> to the pan with a small splash of <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and the <strong>drained spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong></p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> 'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-tomato-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli-with-olive-bruschetta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>and top with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>garlicky ciabatta </strong>with your <strong>black & green olive tapenade </strong>and top with the <strong>bruschetta mix </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>bruschetta</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>bruschetta </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
